ðŸ“Œ Final:
	â€¢	Multiple inheritance with classes leads to ambiguity â†’ âŒ Not allowed.
	â€¢	Interfaces allow multiple inheritance behavior in a clean and conflict-free way.
	â€¢	This is a core OOP concept â€” often asked in Java interviews and system design basics.

